text: Joseph Hardin Coulombe (June 3, 1930February 28, 2020) was an American entrepreneur. His most famous thing he ever did was when he founded the grocery store chain Trader Joe's in 1967.He Brought Trader Joe's to Main Street February 2006 He was born in San Diego, California on June 3, 1930. He was educated at Stanford University. Coulombe died on February 28, 2020 in Pasadena, California at the age of 89. Joseph died of a long illness. The illness that caused his death is unknown or unstated. ==References== Category:1930 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Businesspeople from San Diego
title: Joe Coulombe
